<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<ecoSpold xmlns="http://www.EcoInvent.org/EcoSpold02" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:schemaLocation="http://www.EcoInvent.org/EcoSpold02 ../../schemas/datasets/EcoSpold02.xsd http://www.EcoInvent.org/UsedUserMasterData ../../schemas/datasets/EcoSpold02UserMasterData.xsd">
  <childActivityDataset>
    <activityDescription>
      <activity specialActivityType="0" id="06c7cc00-f16b-5238-be64-a5cae7de93dd" activityNameId="fe14975c-2f49-52d3-a726-0ee9c66618cd" parentActivityId="08307747-4682-50a2-a656-93ec7f272116" inheritanceDepth="-1" type="1">
        <activityName xml:lang="en">zineb production</activityName>
        <synonym xml:lang="en">Polyram</synonym>
        <synonym xml:lang="en">Dithiane Z-78</synonym>
        <synonym xml:lang="en">Aphytora</synonym>
        <synonym xml:lang="en">Amitan</synonym>
        <synonym xml:lang="en">Metiram</synonym>
        <synonym xml:lang="en">1,2 ethanediylbis[dithiocarbamodithioato](2−) zinc</synonym>
        <includedActivitiesStart xml:lang="en">Cradle to gate. The activity starts when the raw materials enter the process.</includedActivitiesStart>
        <includedActivitiesEnd xml:lang="en">Production of zineb production including materials, energy uses, infrastructure and emissions.</includedActivitiesEnd>
        <generalComment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">This dataset represents the production of 1 kg of zineb. Emissions are estimated. Energy consumptions, infrastructure and transports are calculated with standard values. A yield of 95% per chemical step was assumed.</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="1">Zineb is an organic substance with the CAS no.: 012122-67-7. It is called 'zinc ethane-1,2-diylbis(dithiocarbamate)' under IUPAC naming and its molecular formula is: C4H6N2S4Zn. It is solid under normal conditions of temperature and pressure as an offwhite to yellow powder which is insoluble in water and common organic solvents. It is modelled as a pure substance. Zineb is a fungicide used to control mildews and red fire disease in vines, lettuce spinach and many more vegetables. In addition, it can be applied to contron rusts in currants, fruit and vegetables and ornamentals. There are no publicly available information about the consumption of this substance on industrial sites.</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="2">Reference(s):</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="3">Rohe D.M.M., Wolf H.U., (2011). Zinc Compounds. in Ullmanns Encyclopedia of Industrial Chemistry, Weinheim, Wiley-VCH.</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="4">Unger T., (1996). Pesticide Synthesis Handbook, Noyes Publication.</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="5">Ackermann P., Margot P., Muller F., (2011): Fungicides, Agricultural, in Ullmann's Encyclopedia in Industrial Chemistry, Weinheim, Wiley-VCH.</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="6">Chemiepark GENDORF, Umwelterklärung 2016, https://www.gendorf.de/Nachbarn/Umweltschutz/Industrie%20und%20Nachhaltigkeit</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="7">Chemiepark GENDORF, Umwelterklärung 2017, https://www.gendorf.de/Nachbarn/Umweltschutz/Industrie%20und%20Nachhaltigkeit</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="8">Chemiepark GENDORF, Umwelterklärung 2020, https://www.gendorf.de/Nachbarn/Umweltschutz/Industrie%20und%20Nachhaltigkeit</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="9">Hischier, R. (2005) Establishing Life Cycle Inventories of Chemicals Based on Differing Data Availability (9 pp). The International Journal of Life Cycle Assessment, Volume 10, Issue 1, pp 59–67. 10.1065/lca2004.10.181.7</text>
        </generalComment>
      </activity>
      <classification classificationId="28f738cc-bb73-48f8-b633-f83fb9bc5ddc">
        <classificationSystem xml:lang="en">ISIC rev.4 ecoinvent</classificationSystem>
        <classificationValue xml:lang="en">2011:Manufacture of basic chemicals</classificationValue>
      </classification>
      <geography geographyId="34dbbff8-88ce-11de-ad60-0019e336be3a">
        <shortname xml:lang="en">GLO</shortname>
      </geography>
      <technology technologyLevel="3">
        <comment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">This dataset represents the production of 1 kg of zineb.</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="1">Zineb is produced in two steps from ethylene diamine:</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="2">C2H8N2 + 2 CS2 + 2 NaOH → C4H6N2S4Na2 + 2 H2O</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="3">C4H6N2S4Na2 + ZnSO4 → C4H6N2S4Zn + Na2SO4 </text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="4">Reference(s):</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="5">Rohe D.M.M., Wolf H.U., (2011). Zinc Compounds. in Ullmanns Encyclopedia of Industrial Chemistry, Weinheim, Wiley-VCH.</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="6">Unger T., (1996). Pesticide Synthesis Handbook, Noyes Publication.</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="7">Ackermann P., Margot P., Muller F., (2011): Fungicides, Agricultural, in Ullmann's Encyclopedia in Industrial Chemistry, Weinheim, Wiley-VCH.</text>
        </comment>
      </technology>
      <timePeriod startDate="2021-01-01" endDate="2023-12-31" isDataValidForEntirePeriod="true"/>
      <macroEconomicScenario macroEconomicScenarioId="d9f57f0a-a01f-42eb-a57b-8f18d6635801">
        <name xml:lang="en">Business-as-Usual</name>
      </macroEconomicScenario>
    </activityDescription>
